import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';
---
<BlogPostLayout
  title="How to play as UNSC - Halo Wars 2"
  description="Master the UNSC faction in Halo Wars 2 with this beginner's guide covering build orders, unit strategies, turret placement, and army composition tips."
  category="Guides"
  publishedDate="Published on January 31, 2026"
  dateIso="2026-01-31"
  ogImage="/img/HW-Guides/The UNSC - Beginners Guide.png"
  youtubeId="b1RJorPogME"
  tags={['Halo Wars 2']}
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    This guide covers general information for all UNSC leaders. The UNSC has eight leaders: Captain Cutter, Isabel, Professor Anders, and Sergeant Forge (Base Heroes), plus Kinsano, Sergeant Johnson, Commander Jerome, and Serina (DLC Leaders).
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">Early Game Build Order</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Opening Strategy</h3>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Build a Supply Pad immediately</li>
    <li>While the Supply Pad builds, send one Marine squad to gather nearby blue supply crates</li>
    <li>Send your other Marine squad to the furthest power crates on the map</li>
    <li>Once Supply Pad is done, immediately upgrade it to Heavy Supply Pad (you'll have 400 supplies)</li>
    <li>Build a Generator</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Recommended Pad Order</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Supply Pad → Generator → Supply Pad → Supply Pad → Generator (fifth pad)</p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Note:</strong> This is a general build. If you're doing early tactics like a rush or leader build, adjust accordingly.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Leader Point Selection</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">For Captain Cutter: UNSC Raid is better than Battle Hardened</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Critical Early Game Tips</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Generator Management</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Upgrade generators immediately when you have 300 power</li>
    <li>Always upgrade your generators - the 200 power investment pays off</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Mini Bases</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Take mini bases nearby - they provide low-cost extra pads</li>
    <li>Use mini bases to train additional units or boost economy</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">NEVER build a Generator on a mini base</strong>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2">
        <li>Mini bases have less protection than regular bases</li>
        <li>Generators increase in cost (200 → 500 → 800 → 1100 supplies)</li>
        <li>You don't want to lose expensive generators on easily destroyed mini bases</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Good choices for mini bases: Armory, Supply Pads</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Power Nodes</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Power nodes give approximately 1.5 power per second</li>
    <li>May not seem like much, but compounds over 10-15 minutes</li>
    <li>Set rally points near nodes or send starting Marines to capture them</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Turret Placement</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Build turrets for cheap, effective base defense</li>
    <li>To cover your entire base area efficiently, build turrets diagonally</li>
    <li>Place one turret in front on one side, one in the back on the opposite side</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Scouting</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Scout your opponent to understand what they're building</li>
    <li>Get a heads up if they're rushing you</li>
    <li>Use Jackrabbits or Marines to scout</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">UNSC Strengths</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Superior Turrets</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>UNSC turrets are better than Banished turrets</li>
    <li>Banished turrets fire slower and are generally weaker</li>
    <li>UNSC Siege Turrets can protect or even be offensive (depending on map size) without consuming population</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Marines and Snipers</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Marines with Combat Tech upgrade are excellent:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Get rocket launchers for automatic rocket attacks</li>
    <li>Can heal anything mechanical (base, vehicles, even Hornets)</li>
    <li>Almost act as Nightingales</li>
    <li>Only limitation: Can't heal other infantry</li>
    <li>Great cheap option when you need vehicle healing</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Vultures</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Still one of the best units in the game</li>
    <li>Were nerfed slightly but remain very powerful</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Mid-Game Transition</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Expansion</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Start expanding your base once you reach Tech 2</li>
    <li>Grab a second base strategically</li>
    <li>Generally take the nearest expansion base (aggressive expo grabbing is risky)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">The Numbers Game</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Halo Wars 2 is generally a numbers game</li>
    <li>More units typically beats fewer upgraded units</li>
    <li>Not always true, but generally holds</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Production vs Economy Buildings</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>It's actually more beneficial to build more economy buildings (Supply Pads, Generators)</li>
    <li>Multiple production buildings aren't always fully utilized</li>
    <li>Don't miss out on additional resources</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Army Composition</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">General Guidance</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>No definitive upgrade path - depends on the match</li>
    <li>Consider your leaders, allies' leaders, and opponents' leaders</li>
    <li>As the game progresses, move away from counter infantry (Cyclops, Sniper, Hellbringers)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Recommended Late Game Units</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Scorpions</strong>: Great overall unit</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Wolverines</strong>: Mix with Scorpions for anti-air</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Nightingales</strong>: Essential for healing</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Hornets</strong>: Excellent when upgraded with Wingmen and full air upgrades</li>
    <li>Warthogs work well in mid-game, especially for certain playstyles</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Cutter's Cyclops Drop</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the exceptions to weak UNSC counter units</li>
    <li>Drops a Vet 2 Cyclops on the battlefield</li>
    <li>Extremely powerful ability</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">UNSC Weaknesses</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Base Defense</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>No shield generators on base turrets (unlike Banished)</li>
    <li>Can't cloak bases like Banished</li>
    <li>Workaround: Build Nightingales and use their cloak ability on your base (heals too, but temporary)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Counter Units</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">UNSC counter units are weaker than Banished counterparts:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hellbringers &lt; Elite Rangers</li>
    <li>Cyclops &lt; Hunters</li>
    <li>Snipers are an exception - they're really good</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Condor</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Not recommended to build</li>
    <li>Not as good as the Scarab</li>
    <li>Slow and susceptible to attacks</li>
    <li>40 population could be better spent elsewhere</li>
    <li>Air upgrades (Level 1, 2, 3) do NOT apply to the Condor</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">General Tips</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Always Be Active</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Always be doing something</li>
    <li>Get upgrades</li>
    <li>Go on attacks</li>
    <li>Prepare for counterattacks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Map Control</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Take all nodes and mini bases</li>
    <li>Be aggressive</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Know When to Retreat</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Don't be afraid to retreat and rebuild</li>
    <li>If you have a big army you know you'll lose and can't afford to counterattack, regroup and try again</li>
  </ul>
</BlogPostLayout>
